<div class="section">
	<h2>History</h2>
	<div class="section-body">
		<p>MALgraph started as a basic, minimalistic page with black bars (<a target="_blank" href="<?php echo UrlHelper::absoluteUrl('/media/img/history1.png') ?>">version one</a>), and quickly evolved to a full-fledged MAL data parser, a bit richer in colors (<a target="_blank" href="<?php echo UrlHelper::absoluteUrl('/media/img/history2.png') ?>">version two</a>). At some point we realized it had too much information to be shown in a single cluster, so we decided to split it into tabs, thus creating Mg3.</p>
		<p>Continuing the tradition of writing 95% of the code from scratch, Mg4 has been born, with cleaner interface free from clutter and new features suggested by users in <a target="_blank" href="http://myanimelist.net/clubs.php?cid=30017">our&nbsp;club</a>. Even if there aren&rsquo;t many changes visible in the outer layer, the whole engine has been replaced, and a new queuing system has been put to work.</p>
	</div>
</div>

